      "\n",
      "--- Q4: Primary Key Structural Identification ---\n",
      "Primary Keys Identified: customers(customer_id), products(product_id), orders(order_id), order_items(item_id).\n",
      "Explanation: A Primary Key is a foundational relational rule. It must be UNIQUE and NOT NULL to satisfy entity integrity, ensuring that every record can be distinctly identified and preventing corrupt orphaned rows inside database memory.\n",
      "\n",
      "--- Q5: Column Constraint Analysis (Email Field) ---\n",
      "Applied Constraints: UNIQUE and NOT NULL.\n",
      "System Behavior: If an operation attempts to write an identical email string, the transactional layer will instantly trip a 'Constraint Violation Exception' and force an immediate rollback of that statement to protect data sanitization.\n",
      "\n",
      "--- Q6: Active Integrity Constraint Simulation (unit_price = -50) ---\n",
      "[Verification Success] Relational engine safely blocked the operation!\n",
      "Triggered Exception Trace: CHECK constraint failed: unit_price > 0\n",
      "Explanation: The 'CHECK (unit_price > 0)' clause applied to the products table stopped the statement because a value of -50 explicitly breaks the rule.\n"
